From: Keel <ci@keel.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH 0002/0006] keel: prefs: apply Keel defaults at profile creation

Reads the Keel default-pref bundle (../policies/master_preferences.json,
embedded at build time via the BUILD.gn rule added below) and applies it to
the profile's PrefService on first run. The user can still change any of
these after install — this only sets the *defaults*. Managed policies in
../policies/linux/keel-managed-policy.json provide the non-overridable layer.

This file lives entirely in the Brave layer, not Chromium. It does not touch
PrefService internals or registration — only initial values.

---
 brave/browser/brave_browser_main_parts.cc | 12 ++++++++++++
 brave/browser/BUILD.gn                    |  1 +
 2 files changed, 13 insertions(+)

diff --git a/brave/browser/brave_browser_main_parts.cc b/brave/browser/brave_browser_main_parts.cc
--- a/brave/browser/brave_browser_main_parts.cc
+++ b/brave/browser/brave_browser_main_parts.cc
@@
 #include "brave/browser/brave_browser_main_parts.h"
+#include "brave/browser/keel/keel_default_prefs.h"

 void BraveBrowserMainParts::PostProfileInit(Profile* profile,
                                             bool is_initial_profile) {
   ChromeBrowserMainPartsLinux::PostProfileInit(profile, is_initial_profile);
+  if (is_initial_profile) {
+    keel::ApplyKeelDefaultPrefs(profile);
+  }
 }

diff --git a/brave/browser/BUILD.gn b/brave/browser/BUILD.gn
--- a/brave/browser/BUILD.gn
+++ b/brave/browser/BUILD.gn
@@
 source_set("browser_process") {
   sources = [
     "brave_browser_main_parts.cc",
+    "keel/keel_default_prefs.cc",
   ]
 }
